@page "/cards-grid"
<PageTitle>Cards Grid - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="cards-grid">Cards Grid</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The CardsGrid component renders a responsive grid container for Card components.
                Use the framework filter to see how the grid layout is expressed in each design system.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;CardsGrid&gt;
    &lt;Card&gt;
        &lt;CardBody&gt;
            &lt;CardTitle&gt;Card 1&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
            &lt;P&gt;First card content.&lt;/P&gt;
        &lt;/CardBody&gt;
    &lt;/Card&gt;
    &lt;Card&gt;
        &lt;CardBody&gt;
            &lt;CardTitle&gt;Card 2&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
            &lt;P&gt;Second card content.&lt;/P&gt;
        &lt;/CardBody&gt;
    &lt;/Card&gt;
&lt;/CardsGrid&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="related-components">Related Components</h2>

            <ul>
                <li><a href="cards">Card</a> — individual card container.</li>
                <li><code>&lt;CardBody&gt;</code> — card content wrapper.</li>
                <li><code>&lt;CardTitle&gt;</code> — card heading.</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="cards-grid-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Cards Grid</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Cards Grid</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the CardsGrid component maps to a row container with Bootstrap's
                grid classes. Each child Card is wrapped in a column element so the cards flow
                into a responsive multi-column layout. The number of columns adapts at Bootstrap's
                standard breakpoints using the col utility classes defined in the Bootstrap 5
                design system.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="cards-grid-daisyui">DaisyUI Cards Grid</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Cards Grid</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the CardsGrid component uses Tailwind's grid utilities to create a
                responsive card layout. Child Card components receive DaisyUI's card class with
                bg-base-100 and shadow-sm by default. The grid column count responds to the
                viewport width through Tailwind's responsive prefix classes defined in the
                DaisyUI design system implementation.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="cards-grid-basecoat">Basecoat Cards Grid</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Cards Grid</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the CardsGrid component composes a grid layout from Tailwind utility
                classes. The grid gap, column count, and responsive behavior are controlled by the
                Tailwind utilities in the Basecoat design system definition. You can override or
                extend the layout by passing additional Tailwind utilities through the Class or
                Specialization parameters on the CardsGrid component.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("cards-grid", "Cards Grid"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("related-components", "Related Components", 2),
    new TocItem("cards-grid-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Cards Grid", 2),
    new TocItem("cards-grid-daisyui", "DaisyUI Cards Grid", 2),
    new TocItem("cards-grid-basecoat", "Basecoat Cards Grid", 2)
])" />

</div>
